description: Lists the subscription filters for the specified log group. You can list all the subscription filters or filter the results by prefix. The results are ASCII-sorted by filter name.

parameters.name: logGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the log group.

nested_items.name: filterName
nested_items.description: The name of the subscription filter.

nested_items.name: logGroupName
nested_items.description: The name of the log group.

nested_items.name: filterPattern
nested_items.description: A symbolic description of how CloudWatch Logs should interpret the data in each log event. For example, a log event can contain timestamps, IP addresses, strings, and so on. You use the filter pattern to specify what to look for in the log event message.

nested_items.name: destinationArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the destination.

nested_items.name: distribution
nested_items.description: The method used to distribute log data to the destination, which can be either random or grouped by log stream.

nested_items.name: applyOnTransformedLogs
nested_items.description: This parameter is valid only for log groups that have an active log transformer. For more information about log transformers, see PutTransformer.

nested_items.name: creationTime
nested_items.description: The creation time of the subscription filter, expressed as the number of milliseconds after Jan 1, 1970 00:00:00 UTC.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of items to return. The token expires after 24 hours.
